RACE.FOOTNOTES: GLENHOLME was taken back to trail the field into the first turn, was on hold while eager to go on when straightened out to the backstretch, rated kindly four deep outside at the half, offered a bold move five wide at the three furlong pole and wore down multiple rivals down the stretch and was edging away for the win at the finish. MIGHTY PELE broke out but was quickly corrected at the start, prompted outside on the first turn, continued to hound the frontrunner down the backstretch, had a narrow advantage two wide with three furlongs to go, bid three wide with others turning for home, finished gamely through the stretch on the wrong lead, was no match for the winner late but held for the place share at the end. MANETKA was nestled behind the front pair in the beginning, tracked on the fence down the backside watching the leaders, was on hold inside when the field bunched up at the three furlong marker, shifted outside for run at the quarter pole, rallied six wide at the top of the stretch and closed belatedly to capture third money nearing the wire. MOMENT OF ZEN was in a good position tracking the top pair early, kept a close eye on the contesting duo at the half, engaged for the front three wide in a four horse battle at the five sixteenths marker, was in with a shot four wide straightening out for the drive and faded in the final sixteenth. OPEECHEE took this field into the first turn inside, had a slim advantage on the rail down the backstretch, was headed outside by a few rivals midpoint on the far turn, hustled to keep pace at the quarter marker, was in the thick of things at the top of the lane but yielded in the last sixteenth of a mile. DOC FISHMAN was in tight between rivals in the three path into the first turn, travelled in midpack three deep down the backside, could not quicken with others three eighths from the wire and could not be a factor running to the wire. RIVER OF BABYLON was pushed out five wide entering the first turn, could see the field down the back straight, put in a mild run inside midway on the far turn and could not get involved running on the fence through the stretch. PASSIONPLATE settled near the rear on the rail, made little impact close to the back of the pack down the backstretch, was coaxed for more to keep up with runners at the three furlong marker, offered no response and was empty for the stretch drive.

YORKVILLE pressed the winner outside on the turn, was asked left handed but could not get by the winner at the quarter pole and stalled on the fence at the furlong marker. DISCOVERY CHART settled near the back on the rail in the beginning, took some awkward steps on the fence losing action at the seven sixteenths marker and could not regroup to pose a threat in the stretch drive. SECRET CAMELOT prompted on the rail early on, was shuffled back on the fence throughout the turn, shifted five wide off tiring rivals in mid stretch and levelled off at the furlong pole. WONT FORGET YOU tracked in the two path in the beginning, continued to watch the top pair running on the rail throughout the turn and could not find more at the top of the lane and gave way on the fence in mid stretch. FOUR K FORCE was off slow to begin, tugged the rider four deep outside down the back straight to track the top pair through the turn the turn and retreated in upper stretch.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: WOODBINE RACE 10 5 1/2F All Weather Track CR: 62. Maiden Claiming Purse 32800. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000, if for $9,500, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: INFINITE PASSION rated well in hand behind the front group down the back straight, was on hold on the fence behind runners waiting to pounce through the turn, found clear running room in lane five at the top of the stretch and found her best stride at the eighth pole closing strongly to get up in time for the victory. SPEEDY BUBBLES prompted the pace three deep down the back straight, took command with five sixteenths to go, opened up on the field at the top of the lane but could not find another gear late and was caught nearing the wire. TELLTALE was bumped outside at the start, tracked three deep down the backstretch, was in the hunt three wide straightening out for the drive and determinedly finished up between foes to just miss capturing second money at the wire. MISS BIKINI travelled three deep near the front pack down the backstretch, was urged three wide in the mix of things near the lead on the turn, was in contention in the four path turning for home, faded some late between rivals but held for a small share crossing the line. FANCY PHYLLIS settled on the rail near the back at the half mile marker, advanced smartly on the fence throughout the turn, angled seven wide to be in with a chance for a small share turning for home and finished evenly in the final furlong. WANT TO GO DANCING chased on the rail at the half, was in tight behind the top pair with runners on either side midpoint on the turn, found a clear path to run two wide turning for home but could not produce a finish to be in the mix at the end. LULU'S LULLABY was bumped inside on the break, offered a good turn of foot three wide around runners on the turn, shifted out in the six path for the drive but stalled in the final eighth. GUNNAWIN leapt at the start spotting rivals many lengths leaving the gate, finally caught up to runners midway on the turn inside, swung out six wide for the stretch drive, shifted inwards to the rail in the final sixteenth but could not recover from the poor start to be a presence at the finish. SLOANS SKY stalked close to the back at the half, could no make up any ground on others through the turn and passed a straggler in the stretch. MISS BRIANNA took this field down the backstretch on a slim lead, was collared outside three eighths from the finish, was ridden for more trying to keep position and backed away on the fence in upper stretch. SAKE AND SUSHI was away a bit slow to begin, stalked near the rear down the backside, offered a mild brief spurt three wide around horses three furlongs from home and could not find anymore to be involved in the stretch run.
